-- Canada’s Banks Ranked World’s Soundest for Sixth Straight Year
-- B y   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-09-04T19:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-04/canada-s-banks-ranked-world-s-soundest-for-sixth-straight-year.html
Canada’s banking system was ranked
the world’s strongest for the sixth straight year by the World
Economic Forum.  Canada’s banks received the No. 1 spot in the Geneva-based
organization’s Global Competitiveness Report, which was released
today. The  report  includes 148 countries.  “Having a strong and profitable banking system is the
backbone of the Canadian economy,”  Terry Campbell , president of
the Canadian Bankers Association, said in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
